The paper discusses modeling and analyzing cyber-physical systems, which involves the integration of physical and computational components. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.EM (Electromagnetics) sub-category, which deals with the interaction of electromagnetic fields with physical systems. Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of actors to model distributed systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category, which deals with the modeling and control of complex systems. The paper also discusses the use of a specific programming language (Hybrid Rebeca) and the derivation of hybrid automata for analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-categories, respectively. Finally, the paper discusses a case study in the domain of automotive systems, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category, which deals with the development and maintenance of software systems.
